        "# 1. Equation of the Plane Through Points A, B, and C\n",
        "**Question:** Find the equation of the plane passing through points $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$, $$ B(3, 4, 5) $$, and $$ C(2, 1, 4) $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "To find the equation of the plane, we need to compute two vectors on the plane and their cross product to get the normal vector.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Vector $$ \\overrightarrow{AB} = B - A = (3 - 1, 4 - 2, 5 - 3) = (2, 2, 2) $$\n",
        "- Vector $$ \\overrightarrow{AC} = C - A = (2 - 1, 1 - 2, 4 - 3) = (1, -1, 1) $$\n",
        "\n",
        "Now, compute the cross product of $$ \\overrightarrow{AB} $$ and $$ \\overrightarrow{AC} $$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\overrightarrow{AB} \\times \\overrightarrow{AC} =\n",
        "\\begin{vmatrix}\n",
        "\\hat{i} & \\hat{j} & \\hat{k} \\\\\n",
        "2 & 2 & 2 \\\\\n",
        "1 & -1 & 1\n",
        "\\end{vmatrix}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The result is the normal vector $$ \\vec{n} = (4, -4, -4) $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Thus, the equation of the plane is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "4(x - 1) - 4(y - 2) - 4(z - 3) = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Simplify to get the final equation:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x - y - z = -1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visualization:** GeoGebra Link: https://www.geogebra.org/calculator/gvt87ymy\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Equation of the Plane Parallel to $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$\n",
        "**Question:** Find the equation of the plane passing through point $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$ and parallel to the plane $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "The normal vector of the given plane is $$ \\vec{n} = (2, 3, 4) $$, and since the planes are parallel, the new plane will have the same normal vector.\n",
        "\n",
        "Using the point $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$, the equation of the plane is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2(x - 1) + 3(y - 2) + 4(z - 3) = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Simplify to get the final equation:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x + 3y + 4z = 20\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visualization:** GeoGebra Link:https://www.geogebra.org/calculator/rkcjkeg9\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Equation of the Plane Perpendicular to $$ \\vec{n} = [2, 3, 4] $$\n",
        "**Question:** Find the equation of the plane passing through point $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$ and perpendicular to the normal vector $$ \\vec{n} = [2, 3, 4] $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Since the plane is perpendicular to $$ \\vec{n} $$, the normal vector of the plane will be $$ \\vec{n} = (2, 3, 4) $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Using the point $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$, the equation of the plane is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2(x - 1) + 3(y - 2) + 4(z - 3) = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Simplify to get the final equation:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x + 3y + 4z = 20\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visualization:** GeoGebra Link: https://www.geogebra.org/calculator/z3duh57t\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Line of Intersection of Two Planes\n",
        "**Question:** Find the line of intersection of the planes $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$ and $$ 3x + 4y + 2z = 6 $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "To find the line of intersection, we solve the system of equations by eliminating one variable.\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Multiply the first equation by 3 and the second by 2:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "6x + 9y + 12z = 15\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "6x + 8y + 4z = 12\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "2. Subtract the second equation from the first:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(6x + 9y + 12z) - (6x + 8y + 4z) = 15 - 12\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "y + 8z = 3\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Thus, $$ y = 3 - 8z $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Substitute $$ y = 3 - 8z $$ into one of the original equations:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x + 3(3 - 8z) + 4z = 5\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Simplify and solve for $$ x $$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "2x + 9 - 24z + 4z = 5 \\implies 2x = 20z - 4 \\implies x = 10z - 2\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The parametric equations of the line are:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x = 10z - 2, \\quad y = 3 - 8z, \\quad z = z\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Thus, the parametric form of the line of intersection is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(x, y, z) = (-2, 3, 0) + z(10, -8, 1)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visualization:** GeoGebra Link: https://www.geogebra.org/calculator/q2gyzwgx\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. Equation of the Plane Passing Through Point A and Parallel to Vectors $$ \\vec{v}_1 = [1, 0, 1] $$ and $$ \\vec{v}_2 = [0, 1, -1] $$.\n",
        "**Question:** Write the equation of the plane passing through point $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$ and parallel to vectors $$ \\vec{v}_1 = [1, 0, 1] $$ and $$ \\vec{v}_2 = [0, 1, -1] $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "To find the equation of the plane, we need to compute the normal vector by taking the cross product of $$ \\vec{v}_1 $$ and $$ \\vec{v}_2 $$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\vec{v}_1 \\times \\vec{v}_2 =\n",
        "\\begin{vmatrix}\n",
        "\\hat{i} & \\hat{j} & \\hat{k} \\\\\n",
        "1 & 0 & 1 \\\\\n",
        "0 & 1 & -1\n",
        "\\end{vmatrix}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The result is the normal vector $$ \\vec{n} = (1, 1, 1) $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Using point $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$, the equation of the plane is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(x - 1) + (y - 2) + (z - 3) = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Simplify to get the final equation:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x + y + z = 6\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visualization:** [GeoGebra Link]\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# 6. Plane Parallel and Perpendicular to $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$\n",
        "**Question:** Find an example of a plane parallel and perpendicular to the plane $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "- A plane parallel to $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$ will have the same normal vector $$ \\vec{n} = (2, 3, 4) $$ but a different constant. For example, the equation $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 10 $$ is parallel to the given plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "- A plane perpendicular to $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$ will have a normal vector perpendicular to $$ \\vec{n} $$ . For example, the equation $$ x - y + z = 1 $$ is perpendicular to the given plane.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visualization:** [GeoGebra Link]\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# 7. Distance from Point A to the Plane\n",
        "**Question:** Find the distance from point $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$ to the plane $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "The formula for the distance from a point $$ (x_1, y_1, z_1) $$ to a plane $$ Ax + By + Cz + D = 0 $$ is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "d = \\frac{|Ax_1 + By_1 + Cz_1 + D|}{\\sqrt{A^2 + B^2 + C^2}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "For the plane $$ 2x + 3y + 4z = 5 $$, we have $$ A = 2, B = 3, C = 4, D = -5 $$ and point $$ A(1, 2, 3) $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Substitute into the formula:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "d = \\frac{|2(1) + 3(2) + 4(3) - 5|}{\\sqrt{2^2 + 3^2 + 4^2}} = \\frac{|2 + 6 + 12 - 5|}{\\sqrt{4 + 9 + 16}} = \\frac{|15|}{\\sqrt{29}} = \\frac{15}{\\sqrt{29}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visualization:** [GeoGebra Link]\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# 8. Equation of the Plane Intersecting the Coordinate Axes\n",
        "**Question:** Find the equation of the plane that intersects the coordinate axes at points $$ A(2, 0, 0) $$, $$ B(0, 3, 0) $$, and $$ C(0, 0, 4) $$.\n",
        "\n",
        "The equation of a plane that intersects the coordinate axes at points $$ (x_1, 0, 0) $$, $$ (0, y_1, 0) $$, and $$ (0, 0, z_1) $$ is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{x}{x_1} + \\frac{y}{y_1} + \\frac{z}{z_1} = 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Substitute the values $$ x_1 = 2 $$, $$ y_1 = 3 $$, and $$ z_1 = 4 $$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{x}{2} + \\frac{y}{3} + \\frac{z}{4} = 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Multiply through by 12 to clear the denominators:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "6x + 4y + 3z = 12\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Visualization:** [GeoGebra Link]\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
